Rating: 4
Tastes like summer! Please don't use canned tomatoes or frozen corn and then criticize this recipe: it should ONLY be made in the summer, to showcase vine-ripened (preferably heirloom) tomatoes and fresh FRESH corn, cut off the cob right before sauteing. This is essentially, "fresh tomato salad with sauteed fresh corn in it". WONDERFUL.

