Because I love highly seasoned foods and probably have an overstimulated palate, I was underwhelmed by this dish. Were I to make it again, I'd use 1/2 to 3/4 cup of chopped red onion in place of the scallions, toss in a clove or two of minced garlic, and if that didn't liven things up sufficiently, stir in some chopped cilantro and parsley right before serving. (Admittedly, these tweaks would make for a very different salad.)

